    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into chips</p><p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> with 30g <span class=\"text-purple\">[45g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>very cold water </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>batter</strong></p><p>Pat your<strong> hake fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and cut the<strong> fillet[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Sprinkle both sides of the<strong> hake</strong> with <strong>flour</strong> until fully coated</p><p>Dip the<strong> floured hake</strong> into the <strong>batter</strong> and turn it several times until fully coated \u2013 this is your<strong> coated hake</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a medium-sized pot with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced onion </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>then bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has reduced to a thick curry-like consistency</p><p>Once thickened, add the sauce to a <strong>food processor</strong> and blitz until smooth \u2013 this is your<strong> curry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> (enough to coat the base of the pan) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated hake</strong> to the pan and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through, golden and crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>battered fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> brioche halves</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), cut side up, and put the tray[s] in the oven for 4-5 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Combine <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!) and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> in a bowl and season with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> salad</strong> to the bowl and gently mix it all together<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chip-shop-hake-and-chip-burger-with-curry-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, add the<strong> battered fish</strong> to a <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then spoon over some of the <strong>curry sauce</strong>, top with a few of the <strong>chips</strong> and add the <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chip shop hake & chip burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chip shop hake & chip burger </strong>with the<strong> remaining chips</strong>,<strong> dressed salad </strong>and any <strong>remaining curry sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the chips with the<strong> remaining cider vinegar</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
